						               													<description>The Year is 1349 AD. As Gong Fermer inspects his useless crop of rotten vegetables, he simmers with frustration. He&amp;rsquo;s quite aware that he&amp;rsquo;s the poorest, lowliest wretch in this god-forsaken village&amp;mdash;and has the ripe, brown stains on his tattered shirt to prove it. But just to make sure he remembers, the villagers laugh and spit in his face every day, reveling in his misery. As if crappy crops weren&amp;rsquo;t enough!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The excitement begins when Gong decides that he&amp;rsquo;s taken enough crap for one lifetime. Even with the Black Plague killing peasants and noblemen at record speed, Gong decides to take the King&amp;rsquo;s justice into his own hands, with nothing but his battered pride, his trusty dung shovel, and a rusty bucket! The King&amp;rsquo;s battalion of armored knights, archers, and soldiers stand ever ready&amp;hellip; an entire army of seasoned warriors. What chance does Gong have against such wealth and might? Nonetheless, a word festers in the back of Gong&amp;rsquo;s mind: revolt!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You and your friends will have a blast recreating medieval life by playing this fast pace, strategic and addicting card game where nothing is as it seems, nor as it should be.  Instead of singing the praises of &amp;quot;Long live the King&amp;quot;, you will joyfully cry out, &amp;quot;Down with the King, and may Gong Fermer reign!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
